                        <li style="text-align: justify; font-weight: 600;">World-Class Education System
                            <p class="fs-5">Gain a globally recognized qualification from top-ranked universities known for academic excellence and innovation, highly respected by employers worldwide.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="text-align: justify; font-weight: 600;">Unbeatable Career Opportunities
                            <p class="fs-5">Ireland is a European hub for over 1,000 leading multinational companies (tech, pharma, finance). Your degree here opens doors to these global giants.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="text-align: justify; font-weight: 600;">1-Year Master's & 2-Year Post-Study Work Visa
                            <p class="fs-5">Finish your Master's degree efficiently in just one year, then seamlessly transition to a 24-month (2-year) post-study work visa to gain invaluable international experience.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="text-align: justify; font-weight: 600;">Affordable & Competitive Fees
                            <p class="fs-5">Compared to other major English-speaking study destinations, Ireland offers competitive tuition fees and a reasonable cost of living, providing excellent value for your investment.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="text-align: justify; font-weight: 600;">English-Speaking Advantage
                            <p class="fs-5">As the only English-speaking country in the Eurozone, Ireland offers a smooth transition and full immersion, making communication and daily life easy for international students.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="text-align: justify; font-weight: 600;">Flexible Part-Time Work Options
                            <p class="fs-5">Supplement your living expenses by working part-time for up to 20 hours per week during term time, and full-time (40 hours) during official holidays.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="text-align: justify; font-weight: 600;">Safe, Welcoming, & Culturally Rich
                            <p class="fs-5">Experience genuine Irish hospitality in a famously friendly and safe country. Immerse yourself in a vibrant culture with a rich history, music, and arts scene.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="text-align: justify; font-weight: 600;">Gateway to Europe
                            <p class="fs-5"> Ireland's strategic location provides easy and affordable access for travel and exploration across the rest of Europe, broadening your cultural horizons.</p>
                        </li>
